properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 12 at 1:45PM AKST until February 13 at 9:00AM AKST by NWS Fairbanks AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow occurring. Plan on slippery road conditions.
Additional snow accumulations of up to 3 inches are expected,
with storm total accumulation 3 to 5 inches.

* WHERE...Upper Tanana Valley and the Fortymile Country south of
Chicken.

* WHEN...Until 9 AM Thursday.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Look for reduced visibilities at times.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Weather Advisory for snow means periods of snow will
cause travel difficulties. The latest road conditions can be
obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM AKST THURSDAY
